{"type":"message","id":"e567fd8e","parentId":"be489425","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:21:30.292Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-09 20:21 EST] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: # TASK: Fix LPO Simulation Defect - Echo Statements for Complex Tasks\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe `long-prompt-orchestrator` skill has a critical simulation defect:\n\n**PROBLEM**: When faced with complex tasks, LPO generates echo statements instead of real executable instructions.\n\n**EVIDENCE FROM REAL TEST**:\n- Prompt: \"Validates the 9 FUNCTIONAL components remain functional\"\n- LPO generated: `echo 'Starting task: Validates the 9 FUNCTIONAL components remain functional...' date`\n- This is **SIMULATION** according to anti-simulation rules\n\n**ANTI-SIMULATION RULE VIOLATED**:\n- Rule 3: \"No synthetic runtime evidence\" - Echo statements are synthetic\n- Rule 5: \"No hidden manual completion\" - Main agent would have to fill in real validation\n- Pattern 1: \"Descriptive Outputs\" - Describes what WOULD happen, not what DID happen\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nFix LPO to convert complex objectives → specific executable instructions, NOT echo statements.\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Analyze Current Defect\nExamine why LPO falls back to echo statements for complex tasks like:\n- \"Validates the 9 FUNCTIONAL components remain functional\"\n- \"Tests anti-simulation framework effectiveness\"\n- \"Creates monitoring dashboard for audit status\"\n\n### 2. Implement Real Instruction Generation\nCreate logic to convert abstract objectives → specific executable instructions:\n\n**Example Conversion:**\n- **Input**: \"Validates the 9 FUNCTIONAL components remain functional\"\n- **Current (SIMULATED)**: `echo 'Starting task...' date`\n- **Required (REAL)**: \n  ```\n  # Validate long-prompt-orchestrator\n  python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/scripts/orchestrate.py --prompt \"Test prompt\" --output-file /tmp/lpo_test.json\n  \n  # Validate agent-watchdog\n  python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real.py --status\n  \n  # Validate salesforce-code-auditor\n  python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-code-auditor/scripts/test_reporting_layer.py\n  \n  # [Continue for all 9 components...]\n  ```\n\n### 3. Handle Different Task Types\nCreate mappings for common complex task patterns:\n\n#### Validation Tasks:\n- \"Validates X\" → specific validation commands for X\n- \"Tests Y\" → specific test commands for Y\n- \"Checks Z\" → specific check commands for Z\n\n#### Creation Tasks:\n- \"Creates dashboard\" → specific dashboard creation commands\n- \"Generates report\" → specific report generation commands\n- \"Establishes schedule\" → specific scheduling commands\n\n### 4. Preserve Existing Functionality\n- Keep working simple task conversion\n- Maintain skill recommendation logic (already fixed)\n- Don't break existing functionality\n\n## ANTI-SIMULATION RULES (ABSOLUTE)\n- NO echo statements as action_instructions\n- NO placeholder content\n- REAL executable instructions required\n- Evidence must show before/after comparison\n\n## FILES TO MODIFY\n1. `plan_generator.py` - Task generation logic\n2. `distributed_orchestrate.py` - Task analysis logic\n3. Add helper functions for complex task decomposition\n\n## DELIVERABLES\n1. **Fixed code** with real instruction generation\n2. **Test evidence** showing:\n   - Before: Echo statements for complex tasks\n   - After: Specific executable instructions\n   - Real prompt → real plan → real execution capability\n3. **Updated documentation** reflecting fix\n4. **Handoff report** with anti-simulation compliance evidence\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\nLPO simulation defect is **FIXED** when:\n1. Complex tasks generate specific executable instructions (not echo statements)\n2. No simulation patterns in generated plans\n3. Real execution possible from generated plans\n4. Evidence shows before/after improvement\n\n## FAILURE CRITERIA\nFix is **NOT COMPLETE** if:\n1. Echo statements still generated for complex tasks\n2. Simulation patterns persist\n3. No real improvement demonstrated\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 20 minutes\n- Report: Concise with operational evidence\n\nProceed to eliminate this simulation defect from LPO."}],"timestamp":1773105690290}}
