{"type":"message","id":"e24aaf75","parentId":"3b636b85","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:23:23.840Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've confirmed the simulation defect. The issue is in the `_generate_action_instructions` method in `plan_generator.py`. When the action type is \"exec\" and it doesn't match specific patterns (list, search, count, check), it falls back to echo statements.\n\nNow let me analyze the problem and create a fix. The issue is that complex tasks like \"Validates the 9 FUNCTIONAL components remain functional\" don't match any of the specific patterns, so they get generic echo statements.\n\nI need to:\n1. Add pattern matching for complex task types (validation, testing, creation, etc.)\n2. Generate specific executable instructions for each pattern\n3. Ensure no echo statements are generated\n\nLet me examine the current pattern matching logic and create enhanced logic:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_XpjOXEHfeEkyaPuFr4IkKEfn","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/scripts/plan_generator.py","offset":200,"limit":100}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":379,"output":258,"cacheRead":31680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32317,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773105793163}}
{"type":"message","id":"932a950e","parentId":"e24aaf75","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:23:23.856Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_XpjOXEHfeEkyaPuFr4IkKEfn","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"                    return \"ls -la /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace | head -20\"\n            elif \"search\" in obj_lower or \"find\" in obj_lower:\n                # Extract search terms from objective\n                import re\n                terms = re.findall(r'\\\"([^\\\"]+)\\\"|\\'([^\\']+)\\'|for\\s+([a-zA-Z0-9_]+)', objective)\n                search_terms = [term for group in terms for term in group if term]\n                if search_terms:\n                    term = search_terms[0]\n                    return f\"grep -r '{term}' /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace --include='*.md' --include='*.py' | head -10\"\n                else:\n                    return \"grep -r 'TODO\\\\|FIXME' /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace --include='*.py' --include='*.md' | head -10\"\n            elif \"count\" in obj_lower or \"measure\" in obj_lower:\n                if \"line\" in obj_lower:\n                    return \"find /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace -type f -name '*.py' -exec wc -l {} \\\\; | tail -1\"\n                elif \"file\" in obj_lower:\n                    return \"find /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace -type f | wc -l\"\n                else:\n                    return \"find /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace -type f -name '*.py' | wc -l\"\n            elif \"check\" in obj_lower or \"verify\" in obj_lower:\n                return \"python3 -m py_compile /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/*/scripts/*.py 2>&1 | head -10\"\n            else:\n                # Generic command based on objective\n                return f\"# Execute: {objective[:80]}\\necho 'Starting task: {objective[:80]}...'\\ndate\"\n        \n        elif action_type == \"python\":\n            # Generate Python script instructions\n            if \"analyze\" in objective.lower() or \"process\" in objective.lower():\n                return f\"\"\"# Python script to: {objective[:80]}\nimport json\nimport os\nimport sys\n\ndef main():\n    print(\"Analyzing: {objective[:80]}...\")\n    # TODO: Implement analysis logic\n    result = {{\"status\": \"completed\", \"task\": \"{objective[:80]}\"}}\n    \n    # Save output if specified\n    outputs = {outputs}\n    if outputs:\n        with open(outputs[0], 'w') as f:\n            json.dump(result, f, indent=2)\n    \n    return result\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\"\"\"\n            else:\n                return f\"\"\"# Python script to: {objective[:80]}\nimport os\nimport sys\n\ndef main():\n    print(\"Executing: {objective[:80]}...\")\n    # TODO: Implement based on objective\n    return {{\"status\": \"completed\"}}\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\"\"\"\n        \n        elif action_type == \"skill_invocation\":\n            skill = self._recommend_skill_or_role(task_data)\n            if skill == \"tavily-web-search\":\n                # Extract search query from objective\n                import re\n                query_terms = re.findall(r'\\\"([^\\\"]+)\\\"|\\'([^\\']+)\\'|about\\s+([a-zA-Z0-9_\\s]+)', objective)\n                query = next((term for group in query_terms for term in group if term), objective[:50])\n                return f\"Invoke tavily-web-search skill with query: '{query}' --max-results 3 --output /tmp/search_results.json\"\n            elif skill == \"salesforce-architect\":\n                return f\"Invoke salesforce-architect skill with requirement: {objective[:80]}...\"\n            elif skill == \"salesforce-code-auditor\":\n                return f\"Invoke salesforce-code-auditor skill to audit: {objective[:80]}...\"\n            elif skill == \"workspace-janitor\":\n                return \"Invoke workspace-janitor skill to clean up temporary files and organize workspace\"\n            elif skill == \"long-prompt-orchestrator\":\n                return f\"Invoke long-prompt-orchestrator skill to plan: {objective[:80]}...\"\n            elif skill:\n                return f\"Invoke {skill} skill with objective: {objective[:80]}...\"\n            else:\n                return f\"# Determine appropriate skill for: {objective[:80]}\\n# Check available skills in /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/\"\n        \n        elif action_type == \"file_operation\":\n            # Generate file operation instructions\n            if outputs:\n                output_file = outputs[0]\n                if output_file.endswith('.md'):\n                    return f\"\"\"# Create markdown file: {output_file}\ncat > {output_file} << 'EOF'\n# {objective}\n\n{description[:200]}\n\n## Details\n- Created: $(date)\n- Task: {objective[:80]}\n- Status: In progress\n\n## Content\nTODO: Add content based on objective.\nEOF\n\n[382 more lines in file. Use offset=300 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773105803850}}
